&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;Modality LLP is a large-scale provider on NHS community outpatient and diagnostic services. Locally, we offer patients access to community outpatient services across a number of specialty areas including Cardiology, Dermatology, Rheumatology, Pain Management, ENT, Gynaecology, Ophthalmology, Orthopaedics, Paediatrics, Urology and Respiratory Medicine. We also offer a range of diagnostic services including x-ray and ultrasound.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;As we continue to expand, we are looking to recruit to a new vacancy, IT Operations Manager, who will manage and deliver the ICT infrastructure and IT helpdesk function needed for service delivery and integrated patient care. The post holder will lead the IT helpdesk function supporting staff across the LLP and MMS in resolving IT issues and providing core IT training to staff as required. Base location will beOrsborn House, 55 Terrace Road, Birmingham, B19 1BP with some travel required.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;This will be a full time role with some outside hours working on a rota basis.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you would like an informal discussion about the role please email David Palmer, Head of Governance, IT and Estates at david.palmer2@nhs.net &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;The closing date for applications will be &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;Monday 9&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;th&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; November&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
